HEADWORD: York use
<hw>York" use`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The one of the
three printed uses of England which was followed in the north. It was
based on the Sarum use. See <er>Use</er>, <altname>n</altname>.,
6.</def> <rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

